cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DL 

This paper is primarily focused on security and cryptography, which falls under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The paper also discusses the efficiency and deployability of the proposed protocols, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) categories. The paper also presents an implementation and discusses technical issues, which could fall under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the paper uses simulation based on real Internet traffic traces, which could fall under the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) category.
